race.comment: The local Williams yard holds the key. KREON (5) raced in town his first three starts this preparation and then came back home beaten a whisker in this grade bet $2.40F. He led in that and exits from an inside barrier in this. Well-placed to make amends. Stablemate MANWARI (6) brings a string of wins and has delivered comfortably here his last two. Jumped $1.90 the latest and keeps improving. This is stronger but he has to be respected with winning rider McDougall reunited. TONKATSU GODDESS (2) was quickly back on track beaten by 1.4L at Newcastle in better company. The speed-bred mare can use the inside barrier and Collett replaces the apprentice. A serious player. LAMBAY (3) resumes for Canberra's premier stable and is proven fresh. His figures stack up and Owen is a positive jockey engagement. Keep onside.
